{"TopicId":151204,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"RAPIER center of mass","CreatedByName":"edrobotguy","CreatedById":58949,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T08:07:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"edrobotguy","CreatedById":58949,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T08:07:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been trying to make a minimal \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E using the RAPIER engine. \u00A0I found that when adding the engine to the back of my craft the center of mass moved forward. \u00A0Looking at the part definitions, there is no immediately apparent difference between version 1.1.3 and 1.2.0, both of which have a\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCoMOffset = 0.0, 2.6, 0.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daveroski","CreatedById":93896,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T08:29:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe engine had it\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E forward \u003Cu\u003Efor quite a while\u003C/u\u003E. Because of this it was even used to artificially lower the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E on rovers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E forward of the engine allows for the expected weight being behind the engine as the only part you are actually attaching is the exhaust pipe. The engine proper is imagined to be hidden by whatever you attach it to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E forward on a part designed primarily for spaceplanes helps with design where the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E can be too far back to be able to make a comfortable \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T12:28:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the informative post daveroski\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, moving to gameplay questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"edrobotguy","CreatedById":58949,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T20:25:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not a gameplay issue. \u00A0This is a bug. \u00A0I have a very small ship, the Rapier is half the mass of the craft, and the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is in front of the ship. \u00A0The center of mass of the part should be inside the part. If the part is actually longer, make the part\u00A0model longer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-31T20:27:24Z\u0022 title=\u002210/31/2016 08:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by edrobotguy\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daveroski","CreatedById":93896,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T20:50:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222832263\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477945530\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258949\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022edrobotguy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, edrobotguy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not a gameplay issue. \u00A0This is a bug. \u00A0I have a very small ship, the Rapier is half the mass of the craft, and the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is in front of the ship. \u00A0The center of mass of the part should be inside the part. If the part is actually longer, make the part\u00A0model longer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou do have a very small ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA ship with only twice the mass of a Rapier?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually this whole thing has been hashed out quite a while ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome thought as you do. Most did not. The Aye\u0027s had it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FullMetalMachinist","CreatedById":156531,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T21:40:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222832263\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477945530\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258949\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022edrobotguy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, edrobotguy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe center of mass of the part should be inside the part. If the part is actually longer, make the part\u00A0model longer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/124423-the-new-longer-jet-engine-models/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EThey tried\u003C/a\u003E. People complained. I think it\u0027s available as a mod, though.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"edrobotguy","CreatedById":58949,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-01T02:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222832298\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477947033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002293896\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Daveroski\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Daveroski said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou do have a very small ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA ship with only twice the mass of a Rapier?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually this whole thing has been hashed out quite a while ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome thought as you do. Most did not. The Aye\u0027s had it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause I\u0027m trying to make the smallest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E I can.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess it doesn\u0027t matter. \u00A0I can edit the CoMOffset variable myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-01T03:32:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222832362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477950017\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156531\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FullMetalMachinist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, FullMetalMachinist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/124423-the-new-longer-jet-engine-models/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EThey tried\u003C/a\u003E. People complained. I think it\u0027s available as a mod, though.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was fun. \u00A0Almost as much as the changing the ROUND-8 to xenon thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daveroski","CreatedById":93896,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-01T10:04:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222832687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477968796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258949\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022edrobotguy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, edrobotguy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause I\u0027m trying to make the smallest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E I can.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess it doesn\u0027t matter. \u00A0I can edit the CoMOffset variable myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah.. and maybe you can bump up the thrust and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E at the same time and maybe lower the mass a little? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad edrobotguy! (gedit?) Vanilla means vanilla! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Arugela","CreatedById":133381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-01T16:52:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made this for fun after reading this. I don\u0027t think it\u0027s actually the smallest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E based on a rapier. But it\u0027s pretty small. Nuke and rapier. Made it to orbit with\u00A0 300\u002B DeltaV.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/ngxbe92gq99xa8j/Smallest%20SSTO%20Rapier.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/ngxbe92gq99xa8j/Smallest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E Rapier.craft?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s based on a B-52 bomber a little. The wheels or something need to be adjusted to make it take off faster... This would save more fuel at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022photo SMallRapierSSTO_zpszbcnduqv.png\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i1262.photobucket.com/albums/ii613/PicsMe101/KSP/SMallRapierSSTO_zpszbcnduqv.png\u0022 style=\u0022margin-top:2.08333px;width:1000px;height:576px;\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd holy crap. Salvagers Gif changed. No wonder I never recognize him in threads now. I always notice him by his little Gif.. 8)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI forgot about those engine designs. couldn\u0027t they have just let you toggle the long part on and off? Both things could have been achieved... How is this different from toggling shrouds etc.. they should put them back with a toggle so people can get rid of the extended parts if needed for plane designs. Maybe even bend them.... 8o\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-01T17:01:20Z\u0022 title=\u002211/01/2016 05:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 1, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Arugela\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"edrobotguy","CreatedById":58949,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-01T20:30:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222832930\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151204\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477994644\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002293896\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Daveroski\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Daveroski said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah.. and maybe you can bump up the thrust and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E at the same time and maybe lower the mass a little? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad edrobotguy! (gedit?) Vanilla means vanilla! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I know. \u00A0I really wanted to do this in stock. \u00A0That CoMOffset for the Rapier just wreaks havoc with takeoff.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Notepad.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMeh. \u00A0Maybe I can do it without the Rapier.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}